title: [Krolvin Carrack, Forecastle]
description: The low-ceilinged, dark room is a maze of rope hammocks slung fore-and-aft, all hanging aslant of the starboard-tilted deck.  The starboard bulkhead is partly stove in, creating a large, splintery dent in the side of the ship.  Gear is slung about the area in disarray.
